@user, I've got to say, your latest post is just plain wrong. As a hardworking mechanical engineer, I can tell you that your arguments are misguided at best. You're trying to make it sound like socialism is the answer to all our problems, but it's clear you don't understand the principles of capitalism and the free market.

I've been in the workforce for over 20 years, and I've seen firsthand how competition drives innovation and growth. Socialism, on the other hand, stifles creativity and incentive. It's a system that rewards laziness and punishes hard work.

If you want to see real progress, we need to focus on education, job training, and creating a business-friendly environment. Not some utopian fantasy where everyone gets a trophy just for showing up.

@user, I'm not saying we don't have issues to address, but socialism is not the solution. Let's have a real conversation about the issues and find solutions that work for everyone, not just the lazy and entitled.

P.S. - And for the record, I always carry a pocket knife. Just in case I need to cut through the nonsense you're peddling. 😉
